    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Woodrow Wilson</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to the Special Representative</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-07">November 7,
                            1918</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. On second thought it occurs to me that Versailles may be the best place for
                    the peace conference where friendly influences and authorities are in control
                    rather than Switzerland which is saturated with every poisonous element and open
                    to every hostile influence in Europe.<note n="1" xml:id="d77fn1">Regarding
                        proposed locations for the Peace Conference, see also <persName
                            corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel House</persName>’s telegram No. 72, Nov. 9,
                        1918, 4 p.m., <ref target="frus1918Supp01v01#pg_485">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, supp. 1, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 485</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Referring to your number 57<note n="2" xml:id="d77fn2">Not printed.</note> your
                    reply to the French Minister of Foreign Affairs about Austrian forces in the
                    Ukraine I altogether approve.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
